During  the course they continue to study usning the textbook. Grammatical topics  to be learned: towns, shopping, holidays and days off, family, weather and seasons, introducing my town, going out, foreign languages and cultures.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to learn spoken and written Japanese  at the elementary level.  Students practice all four language skills. The aimed level is A1.2.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student who has passed the course is able to: Communicate in a shop at an elementary level, Describe one's usual weekend and describe one's former trip, Introduce one's family in a more detailed way, Have a short conversation on weather topics, Describe one's hometown in more detail and provide instructions how to find a way in the town, Give some advice to a Japanese tourist on places to see and make an appointment with him/her, Recognize about 120 kanji words in provided context.
